<div id="comment_status_65310687" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_65310687" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_65310687" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65310687" name="comment_link_65310687" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23667043&amp;cid=65310687" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65310687)" >Shouldn't Need to File </a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65310687" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65310687); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Insightful)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~nealric">nealric</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~nealric">( 3647765 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65310687">		
		on Wednesday April 16, 2025 @03:32PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23667043&amp;cid=65310687">#65310687</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65310687"><p>In many countries, most individuals don't actually have to file tax returns and the U.S. should follow suit. It's an entirely unnecessary exercise for more than half of individual filers.</p><p>The government already knows how much you made unless you have some unreported income (such as a side hustle) and most individuals no longer itemize deductions. For W-2 employees with wages below a certain point (~$200kish), the government should just send a simple tax statement for you to review in March. If you have nothing additional to declare, you should just be able accept it and receive your refund (or pay additional tax as applicable).</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65310687">
