	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65310813"><p>Nothing is free. But the "free" online filing is cheaper for the government than "free" paper filing. </p><p>More importantly, which costs the American people and taxpayers less? In effect, paying for tax preparation or software is an additional tax. It isn't free and the money comes out of the pockets of the taxpayers directly. </p><p>The IRS ought to just send people a bill with a filled out tax return. For most people, they have all the information they need. </p></div>
	</div>

